snippet.textDisplay:
What's hard about CATS is that you have to know about where it came from. The original musical is adapted from a collection of poems so it really doesn't have much of a story in the first place. The poems reflect about all these types of jellical cats (Rum Tum Tugger, Mr.Mistofolies, Bustofer Jones, etc.) And not so much about what they're doing or where they are. The first few songs in the musical talk about why they gather and who they are, but the rest is mostly up to your imagination.

I mean, I grew up with the 80's film cast version, so I'm already a big fan. But the movie adaptation seems to defile the grave of a production that was actually very innovative for it's time.

The first few songs in the musical talk about why they gather and who they are, but the rest is mostly up to your imagination. 

I mean, I grew up with the 80's film cast version, so I'm already a big fan. But the movie adaptation seems to defile the grave of a production that was actually very innovative for it's time.
